.TH "sof_comp_alloc" 9 "sof_comp_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sof_comp_alloc \- allocate and initialize buffer for a new component
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct sof_ipc_comp *" sof_comp_alloc
.BI "(struct snd_sof_widget *swidget "  ","
.BI "size_t *ipc_size "  ","
.BI "int index "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "swidget" 12
pointer to struct snd_sof_widget containing extended data
.IP "ipc_size" 12
IPC payload size that will be updated depending on valid
extended data.
.IP "index" 12
ID of the pipeline the component belongs to
.SH "RETURN"
The pointer to the new allocated component, NULL if failed.
